 are able, for the best deeds are those done regularly even if they are few.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 8600 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna'ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24300,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/01\/27\/sincerity-allah-only-accepts\/","url_meta":{"origin":23146,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ikhlaas: Allah only accepts sincere good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 27, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Umamah reported: A man came to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, and he said, \u201cIf a man battles for the sake of reward and fame, what do you think he has?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHe has nothing.\u201d The man repeated his question three times, and the\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19696,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/08\/05\/fudayl-on-sunnah\/","url_meta":{"origin":23146,"position":3},"title":"Fudayl on Sunnah: Deeds accepted if sincere and according to Sunnah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Qayyim reported: Fudayl ibn 'Iyad said, \u201cAllah purifies good deeds and makes them correct. Indeed, if deeds are sincere and incorrect, they will not be accepted. If deeds are correct and insincere, they will not be accepted, but rather they are only accepted if they are both sincere and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27953,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/20\/allah-opens-door-argument-action\/","url_meta":{"origin":23146,"position":4},"title":"Ma&#8217;ruf on Arguing: If Allah guides him, he acts and does not argue","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 20, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Nu\u2019aym reported: Ma\u2019ruf al-Karkhi, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cIf Allah wills goodness for a servant, He opens the door of action and closes the door of disputation. If Allah wills harm for a servant, He closes the door of action and opens the door of disputation.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36990,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/09\/25\/khawatim-determine-akhirah\/","url_meta":{"origin":23146,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Khawatim: Final deeds determine fate in Hereafter","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 25, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Sahl ibn Sa\u2019d reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, the deeds are only judged by their endings.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6607 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari Imam Ibn al-Mulaqqin commented, \"Allah judges His servants in good and evil, such that He forgives\u2026","re